---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import siteConfig from "../data/site-config.json";

const currentYear = new Date().getFullYear();
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`About ${siteConfig.brand.name} | Static Horror Game Guides`}
  description="About Horrordex, a static horror game and Backrooms guide archive for entity dossiers, platform guides, and game recommendations."
  current="none"
>
  <main class="site-shell legal-shell">
    <article class="article-body legal-page">
      <p class="eyebrow">COMPLIANCE FILE / ABOUT</p>
      <h1>About Horrordex</h1>
      <p class="lead">
        Horrordex is a static guide archive for Backrooms lore, Roblox horror, browser games, Minecraft survival,
        and curated horror game recommendations.
      </p>

      <h2>Editorial Scope</h2>
      <p>
        The site is built around practical discovery pages: entity dossiers, survival guides, ranked lists, platform
        primers, FAQ sections, and source attribution. Content is generated into static pages so it can load quickly
        without a runtime server.
      </p>

      <h2>How Content Is Updated</h2>
      <p>
        Guides and data files are reviewed during the static content pipeline. The {currentYear} update cycle focuses on
        clearer platform coverage, stable URLs, image attribution, internal links, and reader-facing explanations that
        make each page useful beyond a keyword list.
      </p>

      <h2>Advertising Disclosure</h2>
      <p>
        Horrordex may display advertising through Google AdSense. Ad placements are kept separate from editorial copy
        and are labeled through reusable static components.
      </p>

      <h2>Corrections</h2>
      <p>
        Game platforms and availability can change. If a link, title, or recommendation becomes outdated, corrections
        should be made in the content files and shipped through the static deployment workflow.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
